# ============================================================
# TRADE CORE ARCHITECTURE
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: architecture
domain: trade
scope: trade.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines the canonical architectural role of trade in CivilizationOS.

## design_intent
Trade is the bounded exchange relationship
between actors and/or institutions
under declared scope,
declared terms,
declared authority,
and reviewable outcomes.

Trade is not the same as market visibility.
Market may expose opportunity,
but trade is the governed exchange act.

## architectural_position
Trade connects:
- company supply
- market discovery
- actor demand
- item/service exchange
- policy/governance boundary
- financial/economic consequence

## required_behavior
- trade identity must remain explicit
- trade parties must remain explicit
- exchange scope must remain explicit
- authority and approval basis must remain explicit
- current and historical trade states must remain distinguishable

## state_model
The trade domain distinguishes:
- proposed trade
- pending trade
- approved trade
- active trade
- disputed trade
- closed trade
- historical trade

## canonical_rules
- trade proposal does not imply approved trade
- exchange authority must remain explicit
- disputed and closed states must remain distinguishable
- historical trade trace must remain preserved
- ambiguous trade authority fails closed

## actor_boundary
- offering party
- receiving party
- operator
- reviewer
- approver
- adapter

## review_checklist
- party model is explicit
- trade states are explicit
- authority basis is explicit
- dispute handling is explicit
